step.context:
\text{If there are x cakes of the first kind and}\\
\text{y cakes of the second kind, what do we}\\
\text{need to maximise?}

\text{For the above constraints, what does the plot }\\
\text{representing the feasible region and its corner }\\
\text{points look like?}

step.reason:
\text{Since the feasible region is bounded, we can}\\
\text{establish the maximum by substituting corner} \\
\text{points in the objective function.}
